      <acqinfo id="aspace_5b1a3ee15becf8db8780f36e46cef40c">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Gift of Mr. and Mrs. Horace Healey, 1939.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <prefercite id="aspace_5872d02e49732c671de878b2a64c8124">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Horace Grant Healey Papers. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_df70aa0859504e1c5446e7a670904c5c">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Horace Grant Healey was an assistant in charge of secretarial studies at Evander Childs High School in New York City. He was also editor of Penman's Art Journal for sixteen years. Healy died on December 9, 1938, in St. Petersburg, Florida.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_a7fb390bc41a241204be7059d63b4006">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>These papers consist of one manuscript notebook, twenty typescript notebooks, and two scrapbooks for a history of shorthand by Horace G. Healey. The book was never published.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
